# Intuition & Approach
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
I will find lexographically greatest subsequence from both array and then merge them.
But constraint is length=k must be satisfied. So have to find lexographically greater subsequence such that both combinedly have length k.

But how to decide how much length have to take from first array and how much from second array? --> This time go by bruteforce. So for possible {i, k-i} pair of length , we will find our answer.

let's divide the problem into subparts:
subpart-1: find out lexographically greatest subsequence from both array.
subpart-2: Merge them and keep taking maximum.

Implemented stack logic through array. You can go through stack .
# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(K*N + K*N)= O(K*N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(K) => for this loop: for(int i=0;i<=k;i++) in maxNumber function.
O(N) => for getGrtrSubseq function.
O(K*N) => merge Function.
- Space complexity: O(N) as all are linear vectors.
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

