# Desc
Create an unordered_map called visited to keep track of the combinations that have been visited. Initialize all combinations in visited with a value of true using the deadends input.

Check if the starting combination "0000" is present in visited. If it is, that means it is a deadend, and we return -1.

Initialize a variable ans to 0, which will represent the minimum number of moves needed to reach the target combination.

Create a queue called q and push the starting combination "0000" into it.

Perform a breadth-first search (BFS) traversal using the queue q to explore all possible combinations.

In each iteration of the BFS loop:

Get the current combination from the front of the queue.
If the current combination is equal to the target combination, we have found the target, so we return the value of ans.
Generate the eight neighboring combinations by incrementing or decrementing each digit of the current combination.
For each neighboring combination, check if it has not been visited before. If it is a new combination, mark it as visited by updating visited and enqueue it into q for further exploration.
Repeat this process for all combinations in the current level of the BFS traversal.
If we exhaust all possible combinations without finding the target, we return -1 to indicate that the target cannot be reached.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int openLock(vector<string>& deadends, string target) {
        unordered_map<string , bool>visited;
        for(string it : deadends){
            visited[it] = true;
        }
        if(visited["0000"] == true)
            return -1;
        int ans = 0;
        queue<string>q;
        q.push("0000");
        while(!q.empty()){
            int n = q.size();
            for(int i = 0 ; i < n ; i ++){ 
                string temp = q.front();
                q.pop();
                if(temp == target) return ans;   

                for(int j = 0 ; j < 4 ; j ++){
                    string fwd = temp , bwd = temp;

                    fwd[j] < '9' ? fwd[j]++ : fwd[j] = '0';

                    bwd[j] > '0' ? bwd[j]-- : bwd[j] = '9';

                    if(!visited[fwd]) {
                        visited[fwd] = true;
                        q.push(fwd);
                    }
                    if(!visited[bwd]) {
                        visited[bwd] = true;
                        q.push(bwd);
                    } 
                }

            }
            ans++;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
