solutions.content:
```
Let's say target = '7120'

As the target starts with '7', obviously we have to go by 
   '9000' --> '8000' --> '7000' --> '7100' --> '7110' --> '7120' --> '7120'
But what if all of those string are already in "deadends"? Then maybe the shortest way from
'1000' .....

So we've to check every possible combination level by level which is BFS.

                    '0000'

'1000'      '0100'      '0010'       '0001' [YOU CAN GET THESE BY FLIPPING ONCE FROM '0000']

I can put 1 in any of these way. This is forward but in backward there might be short path,
so we also need to go backward also.

'9000'      '0900'      '0090'       '0009' [YOU CAN GET THESE BY FLIPPING ONCE FROM '0000']


                From    '1000' the below 4 type string we can get :

2000         1100        1010         1001  [YOU CAN GET THESE BY FLIPPING TWICE FROM '0000']
             |__________________________|
                    |--- Some combinations with only 1

This way from 0100, 0010 and 0001 we will find some string with 1s.
You can clearly see we will have all type of combinations slowly LEVEL BY LEVEL.

HERE IN THIS BFS EACH 'LEVEL' REPRESENTING WHATEVER STRING WE CAN GET IN THIS LEVEL BY 
TURNING ONE CHARACTER INTO ANOTHER 'IS THE MINIMUM TURNS REQUIRED TO GET THOSE STRINGS' and 
if any of these string == target, we return the level.
----

```
```CPP []
class Solution {
public:
    int openLock(vector<string>& deadends, string target) 
    {
        if(target == "0000") return 0;
        unordered_set<string> visited(begin(deadends), end(deadends));
        if(visited.count("0000")) return -1;

        queue<string> q(deque<string> {"0000"});
        string main, cur, prev;

        for(int size = 1, level = 1; !q.empty(); size = q.size(), level++)
        {
            while(size--) 
            {
                main = cur = prev = q.front(); q.pop();
                for(int i=0; i<4; i++)
                {
                    cur[i] += (cur[i] == '9'? -9 : 1);
                    if(cur == target) return level;
